WEBVTT

00:05.603 --> 00:09.575
Look, there's been some kind
of misunderstanding, all right?

00:09.577 --> 00:11.310
I'm innocent!

00:11.312 --> 00:13.105
I didn't--I--

00:13.107 --> 00:16.600
I couldn't do this!

00:16.602 --> 00:19.980
Will someone please
listen to me!

00:24.351 --> 00:25.820
Who are you?

00:25.822 --> 00:27.716
I'm Agent Hotchner,
Mr. Merrin.

00:27.718 --> 00:29.851
Have you been advised
of your rights?

00:29.853 --> 00:32.353
Yeah.

00:32.354 --> 00:34.754
Do you know where you are?

00:36.263 --> 00:38.575
Some FBI place, right?

00:38.577 --> 00:41.546
You're at the Behavioral
Analysis Unit in Quantico, Virginia.

00:41.548 --> 00:43.487
You know why you're here?

00:43.489 --> 00:45.794
Because you think
I'm a killer.

00:45.796 --> 00:47.427
Are you a killer?

00:47.429 --> 00:48.564
No.

00:48.566 --> 00:51.133
Why won't anybody believe me?
I am not--

00:51.135 --> 00:53.102
Stop.

00:53.104 --> 00:54.940
Sit down.

01:00.645 --> 01:02.841
Take a deep breath.

01:04.913 --> 01:08.079
I want you to tell me exactly
what happened two nights ago.

01:08.081 --> 01:10.141
Don't leave anything out.
Can you do that?

01:10.143 --> 01:14.081
Yeah.
Yeah, I can do that.

01:16.980 --> 01:21.154
So, uh, me and...

01:21.156 --> 01:24.122
me and my wife Tabitha,

01:24.124 --> 01:27.092
we were getting ready
for bed and she says...

01:27.094 --> 01:28.865
I think I heard something,

01:28.867 --> 01:30.306
downstairs.

01:30.308 --> 01:32.373
Again?
Maybe outside.

01:32.375 --> 01:35.583
It's--it's a dog or a cat or squirrel
or something.

01:35.585 --> 01:36.920
It's nothing.

01:36.922 --> 01:38.854
Go.

01:42.067 --> 01:43.729
So I did.

01:45.000 --> 01:51.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:53.839 --> 01:57.443
I checked the front door
and it was fine.

01:59.076 --> 02:01.144
Everything was fine.

02:02.148 --> 02:04.378
Until...

02:04.380 --> 02:08.985
Until I--I smelled
like...sage.

02:08.987 --> 02:10.553
Sage?

02:10.555 --> 02:14.385
Like the burning sage.

02:14.387 --> 02:16.722
'Cause that's when I...

02:39.193 --> 02:40.831
Tabitha?!

02:40.833 --> 02:42.462
Hold on! I'm--

02:45.969 --> 02:47.568
Aah!

02:50.909 --> 02:52.780
A shadow monster?

02:52.782 --> 02:54.782
Yeah.

02:54.784 --> 02:56.784
With talons for hands?

02:56.786 --> 02:59.193
I know how it sounds.

02:59.195 --> 03:03.128
I--I knew I needed
to get upstairs,

03:03.130 --> 03:06.159
because...

03:07.329 --> 03:09.464
Because I--I--

03:09.466 --> 03:12.272
I could
hear her screaming.

03:12.274 --> 03:13.808
Larry, no!

03:13.810 --> 03:16.811
Larry, please, stop!

03:18.583 --> 03:20.014
No! No! No!

03:20.016 --> 03:23.023
No! No! Larry, please!

03:23.025 --> 03:25.422
No! Larry, no!

03:25.424 --> 03:27.787
Please don't! Larry, no!

03:30.092 --> 03:31.257
Stop, Larry!

03:31.259 --> 03:33.060
Stop! Aah!

03:47.875 --> 03:49.345
I passed out,

03:49.347 --> 03:52.714
and when I woke up,
the cops had arrested me.

03:54.149 --> 03:55.884
I didn't do it.

03:55.886 --> 03:59.755
I swear to God, it is
exactly what happened.

03:59.757 --> 04:01.692
No, it's not.

04:01.694 --> 04:03.124
Yes, it is.

04:03.126 --> 04:05.792
Mr. Merrin, what happened
was you took a kitchen knife

04:05.794 --> 04:07.359
and you stabbed
your wife to death.

04:07.361 --> 04:08.959
No, no.

04:08.961 --> 04:11.895
Neighbors heard the screaming
and they called 911,

04:11.897 --> 04:14.496
and when the police arrived,
they found you still on the bed

04:14.498 --> 04:15.737
holding the knife.

04:15.739 --> 04:17.200
I didn't do that.

04:17.202 --> 04:19.007
You've been scratching
yourself, Mr. Merrin.

04:19.009 --> 04:21.541
Are you aware of that?

04:21.543 --> 04:23.604
Open your shirt
and you will see why.

04:26.509 --> 04:29.506
That's--that's from
the shadow monster.

04:29.508 --> 04:31.042
No, that's from your wife.

04:31.044 --> 04:33.114
Forensics matched your skin
under her fingernails

04:33.116 --> 04:35.913
as she fought to keep you
from killing her.

04:35.915 --> 04:38.414
Think back to the words
she was screaming.

04:38.416 --> 04:42.179
Larry, please, please,
please! Larry!

04:44.186 --> 04:45.184
Larry...

04:45.186 --> 04:47.279
Why would I do that?

04:48.785 --> 04:52.623
Do you recognize
either of these people?

04:52.625 --> 04:54.623
No, I--no.

04:54.625 --> 04:58.294
This is Daniel Karras
and this is Christine McNeil.

04:58.296 --> 05:00.632
Each of them claims to have
been attacked in their homes

05:00.634 --> 05:02.098
by a shadowy figure.

05:02.100 --> 05:05.273
When in reality, Daniel
stabbed his mother to death

05:05.275 --> 05:06.936
and Christine her boyfriend.

05:06.938 --> 05:10.842
And like you, they have no
recollection of the murders.

05:10.844 --> 05:13.283
What does it mean?

05:13.285 --> 05:14.779
It means that someone
found a way

05:14.781 --> 05:17.050
to induce a psychotic break
in the 3 of you.

05:17.052 --> 05:19.186
Why--why us? Why me?

05:19.188 --> 05:21.490
Well, that's why you're here
instead of a holding cell in Topeka,

05:21.492 --> 05:24.826
so my team can answer
that question.

05:24.828 --> 05:26.322
Agent Hotchner.

05:28.730 --> 05:30.424
I'm not a murderer.

05:30.426 --> 05:31.791
Yes, you are.

05:31.793 --> 05:34.093
And I'm going to find out
who turned you into one.

