that they were.

20:15.383 --> 20:17.421
Is this important?

20:18.958 --> 20:21.291
All right, let's assume
all the victims share

20:21.293 --> 20:23.624
Bill Kinderman's propensity
for recovered memories.

20:23.626 --> 20:25.053
What does that mean
for the unsub?

20:25.055 --> 20:27.252
It means his drugs would have
more of an effect on them.

20:27.254 --> 20:29.091
Why them more than
a normal person?

20:29.093 --> 20:31.722
Because when something's remembered
for the first time on a therapist's couch,

20:31.724 --> 20:35.193
